HEADWORD: Lantanuric
<hw>Lan`ta*nu"ric</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Formed by
transposition of the letters of <ets>allantoin</ets> and
<ets>-uric</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Pertaining to, or
designating, a nitrogenous organic acid of the uric acid group, obtained
by the decomposition of allantoin, and usually called
<altname>allanturic acid</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

